Both the `for` and `while` loops in the code cause the program to run indefinitely. The first `break;` statement in the solution will allow the program to exit the `while` loop and the second `break;` statement in the solution will allow the program to exit the `for` loop. In order for `Print me!` to be printed, the `break;` statement must go *after* the print statement.

